{#
Bootstrap Home: https://getbootstrap.com

You can opt to use the CDN version of Bootstrap by setting your
configuration (extensions.json) file to:

    "install": true,   <--- Will enable Bootstrap
    "local": false,    <--- Will look for Bootstrap on CDN

If you prefer to use the CDN version, just you must remove the Bootstrap
entry from the "composer.json" file.

REQUIRED: If you don't already have it set in your META tags configuration,
uncomment the two <meta> lines below:
#}
{#   <meta charset="utf-8"> #}
{#   <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no"> #}

{% if boilerplate.settings.extensions.bootstrap.install %}
    <!-- Bootstrap Local (via COMPOSER) -->
    <link href="{{vendor}}/twbs/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
{% else %}
    <!-- Bootstrap's CSS file (via CDN) -->
    <link
        href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/{{boilerplate.settings.extensions.bootstrap.version}}/css/bootstrap.min.css"
        integrity="{{boilerplate.settings.extensions.bootstrap.css_integrity}}"
        crossorigin="anonymous"
        rel="stylesheet">
{% endif %}
